title: For Sale:  ZEN AND THE ART OF SHOOTING
location: NW COLORADO SPRINGS, Colorado Springs, Colorado
postcontent:
At first, shooting is 90% technique.  Once mastered, it is 100% mental.

Have you ever been in the zone when every thing slows down and your subconscious takes over?  You need that zone to shoot well.  Once you have mastered the Grip, trigger control and sight picture it is time to clear you mind and let your right and left brain work together to land perfect shots.  

Anyone can learn to shoot accurately.  If you are trying to shoot well, it is the trying that is holding you back.  Do not try- do.

The 2-hour class includes personal instruction and range time.  It is limited to 2 people.    A larger group can be scheduled if it is a family.  The time also increases.

The cost is per hour.  All material and range time is included.

For an additional $35 per student, the class can be extended to include the NRA Handgun Class that qualifies for the Colorado Concealed Permit.

I am an NRA Certified Pistol Instructor and active Rifle and Pistol Competitor.

title: For Sale:  French Model 1936 MAS Manufactured d' Aemes de Saint-Etienne
postcontent: This was the French's main Battle Rifle in WWII. Before you say anything remember there were over 3 million men fighting for the Free French with the Allies. This rifle was also used by the French during the Korean War and during their time in Vietnam. In the mid 50s in order to conform to NATO regulations the French rechambered their weapons to 7.62x51mm (308). The Model 1936 were selected as their Sniper Rifle when they switched to a semi-auto MBR. Because this rifle has been drilled for the standard French military side scope mount this was one of the rifles selected as a sniper rifle. I have found the side mount and have put a Bushnell 3x-9x40 scope on it. The original were Leapers. Also it has a lace on cheek plate.

Is a Salt Bath Nitride Finish surface conversion process or more commonly referred to as Nitriding.
